name: nucleotide diphosphatase
reaction: a nucleoside triphosphate + H2O = a nucleotide + diphosphate [RN:R01532]
comment: The enzyme preferentially hydrolyses ATP, but can also hydrolyse other nucleoside 5' triphosphates such as GTP, CTP, TTP and UTP to their corresponding monophosphates. In vitro the enzyme also acts as a nucleotidohydrolase on ADP, NAD+, NADP+, FAD, and CoA.
